    11	---
    12	
    13	# Lane C Skill-Benchmark Operator Guide
    14	
    15	Lane C benchmarks whether a *skill* is well-routed, discoverable, efficient, and useful **in practice** — distinct from `sk-doc`/`validate.sh` (doc shape) and manual testing playbooks (described behavior). It emits a ranked, remediable Skill Benchmark Report.
    16	
    17	---
    18	
    19	## 1. OVERVIEW
    20	
    21	Run Lane C with `loop-host.cjs --mode=skill-benchmark` (or `/deep:start-skill-benchmark-loop`). The orchestrator runs the D5 structural hard gate first, then per-scenario contamination-lint → router-replay → score, then writes a dual JSON+Markdown report. Mode A is deterministic and is the CI gate; the D1-inter advisor probe and live trace are opt-in / follow-on.
    22	
    23	## 2. INVOCATION
    24	
    25	```bash
    26	# Mode A (router-replay, deterministic — the CI gate). Run on a skill that has an
    27	# INTENT_SIGNALS + RESOURCE_MAP smart router in its SKILL.md.
    28	node .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs \
    29	  --mode=skill-benchmark \
    30	  --skill=<skill-id-or-root> \
    31	  --outputs-dir=<path> \
    32	  [--fixtures-dir=<path>] [--trace-mode=router] [--advisor-mode=python]
    33	```
    34	
    35	`--advisor-mode=python` enables the **D1-inter** advisor probe — the deterministic in-repo SQLite advisor, scored out-of-band so the answer cannot leak. It is **off by default** (and in CI) to keep the pure-router path fast and dependency-free; enable it to lift a Mode A run from 4-dimension to 5-dimension coverage.
    36	
    37	Command surface: `/deep:start-skill-benchmark-loop` (see `commands/deep/start-skill-benchmark-loop.md`).
    38	
    39	## 3. WHAT RUNS (MODE A)
    40	
    41	1. **D5 connectivity** (static, hard gate) — runs first; dead routed paths, dead intent keys, path escapes, orphan refs, unparseable router. Any P0 caps the verdict to `BLOCKED-BY-STRUCTURE`.
    42	2. **Fixtures** — public/private pairs under `assets/skill-benchmark/fixtures/<skill-id>/` (`<id>.public.json` + `<id>.private.json`).
    43	3. **Per scenario** — contamination-lint the public prompt (a leak is a fixture failure), then router-replay, then join with private gold to score.
    44	4. **Report** — `skill-benchmark-report.json` + `skill-benchmark-report.md` (rendered FROM the JSON, anti-drift).
    45	
    46	## 4. DIMENSIONS
    47	
    48	| Dim | What | Mode A |
    49	| --- | ---- | ------ |
    50	| D1-intra | in-skill router selects expected intents/resources | scored |
    51	| D2 | unprompted discovery (router-replay recall proxy) | scored |
    52	| D3 | efficiency (over-routing proxy) | scored |
    53	| D5 | structural connectivity | scored (hard gate) |
    54	| D1-inter | advisor selects the right skill | scored when `--advisor-mode=python` (else `unscored-mode-a`) |
    55	| D4 | usefulness via skill-on/off ablation | unscored (needs live mode) |
    56	
    57	D1-inter is **built and deterministic** but opt-in (`--advisor-mode=python`). Only D4 and the live in-situ trace (Mode B) remain follow-on — see the 002 implementation playbook. Mode A is honest about its coverage: the aggregate normalizes over the dimensions actually measured.
    58	
    59	## 5. VERDICT BANDS
    60	
    61	`PASS` ≥80 & no gate · `CONDITIONAL` 50–79 · `FAIL` <50 · `BLOCKED-BY-STRUCTURE` on any D5 P0. (Provisional — calibrate on 2-3 pilots.)
    62	
    63	## 6. TARGET ELIGIBILITY
    64	
    65	Mode A needs a parseable `INTENT_SIGNALS` + `RESOURCE_MAP` router (e.g. the `cli-*` skills). Skills without that pattern report `router_unparseable` and gate — that is a real signal that the skill is not smart-router-routable, not a harness bug. A skill that routes via a different mechanism is a candidate for live-mode (Mode B) measurement once built.

