.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md:8:Copy-paste pseudocode patterns that make a skill's smart router survive reference and asset changes (renames, deletes, new project folders, missing files) without crashing or silently degrading.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md:10:## 1. OVERVIEW
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md:14:Smart routers fail when resource paths drift, reference folders are deleted, static file lists go stale, or routing logic assumes one hardcoded project or mode forever. This asset packages the canonical four-pattern fix: every routing call discovers the current markdown inventory, guards paths inside the skill folder, loads only files that still exist, selects resources from a runtime-derived routing key, and returns useful fallback guidance instead of crashing or silently loading nothing.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md:28:- Do not maintain static lists of every reference or asset file
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md:29:- Recursive `rglob("*.md")` under `references/` and `assets/`
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md:37:RESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / "references", SKILL_ROOT / "assets")
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md:73:- Key selects a subdirectory under `references/<key>/` and `assets/<key>/`
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md:86:reference_prefix = f"references/{routing_key}/"
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md:88:keyed_refs = sorted(path for path in inventory if path.startswith(reference_prefix))
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md:141:| Git remote | Project or repository routing | `references/<repo>/`, `assets/<repo>/` |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md:142:| Intent label | Workflow or document-family routing | `references/<intent>/`, `assets/<intent>/` |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md:143:| Stack marker | Tooling or language routing | `references/<stack>/`, `assets/<stack>/` |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md:144:| Environment variable | Runtime mode or deployment routing | `references/<mode>/`, `assets/<mode>/` |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md:145:| Command suffix | Subcommand variant routing | `references/<variant>/`, `assets/<variant>/` |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md:146:| Task field override | Explicit caller-supplied routing | `references/<override>/`, `assets/<override>/` |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md:155:- Build `RESOURCE_BASES` from skill-local `references/` and `assets/` only
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md:181:- Raw `load("references/file.md")` calls without guard, inventory check, or duplicate suppression
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md:184:- Loading from `references/` or `assets/` without sandboxing paths to the current skill folder
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md:192:The router discovers reference and asset docs dynamically. Start with `skill_md_template.md`, `skill_asset_template.md`, and `skill_reference_template.md`, then load task-specific examples or source patterns only when needed.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/flowcharts/user_onboarding.md:7:## 1. OVERVIEW
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/flowcharts/user_onboarding.md:33:                                      │ Preferences  │
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/readme_creation.md:18:## 1. OVERVIEW
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/readme_creation.md:20:This reference defines standards for README documentation. READMEs are the entry point to any project, component or feature. They answer "What is this?" and "How do I use it?" in a scannable, progressive format.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/readme_creation.md:56:| **Project** | `/README.md` | New contributors, evaluators | Two-tier (narrative + reference) |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/readme_creation.md:57:| **Skill** | `.opencode/skills/[name]/README.md` | Humans understanding the skill | Two-tier (narrative + reference) |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/readme_creation.md:58:| **Feature** | `/docs/features/[name]/README.md` | Developers implementing or maintaining | Two-tier (narrative + reference) |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/readme_creation.md:59:| **Component** | `/src/components/[name]/README.md` | Developers using the component | Technical (reference only) |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/readme_creation.md:60:| **Code Folder** | `[code-dir]/README.md` | Developers reading or modifying code | Technical (reference only) |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/readme_creation.md:79:**Reference tier** -- precise parameter tables, configuration flags, tool signatures. Terse and scannable. Appears in the reference half of Features (e.g., "3.2 Tool Reference"), Configuration and Related Documents.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/readme_creation.md:81:Project, Skill and Feature READMEs use both tiers. Component and Code Folder READMEs use the reference tier only.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/readme_creation.md:113:Split into a narrative subsection (`### 3.1 HOW IT WORKS`) and a reference subsection (`### 3.2 TECHNICAL REFERENCE`). Use numbered H3 ALL CAPS subsections with `---` dividers between them. Use numbered H4 ALL CAPS sub-subsections (3.1.1, 3.1.2) within narrative subsections.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/readme_creation.md:123:**Purpose**: Complete configuration reference.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/readme_creation.md:170:| **H2** | Numbered, ALL CAPS | `## 1. OVERVIEW` |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/readme_creation.md:209:Tables are scannable. Use them for feature comparisons, configuration options, file listings, requirements and quick reference data.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/readme_creation.md:249:**Parameter** -- Reference-tier table. Use in Features reference subsections and Configuration.
