.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/skill_creation.md:12:## 1. OVERVIEW
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/skill_creation.md:14:Level 3 reference for the full skill lifecycle: creation, validation, and distribution.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/skill_creation.md:24:Skills are modular packages that extend an AI agent with specialized workflows, tool integrations, domain expertise, and bundled resources (scripts, references, assets).
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/skill_creation.md:42:    ├── references/       - Documentation (flat or domain subfolders)
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/skill_creation.md:44:        ├── skill/         - Skill creation templates (SKILL.md, README, reference, asset)
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/skill_creation.md:50:- **references/** = flat for small skills, domain subfolders for medium/complex skills
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/skill_creation.md:51:  - Grouped example: `references/global/core_standards.md`, `references/global/validation.md`
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/skill_creation.md:52:  - Domain example: `references/backend/go/`, `references/frontend/react/`
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/skill_creation.md:85:- Readers need a concise map that explains how `SKILL.md`, `references/`, `assets/` and `scripts/` fit together.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/skill_creation.md:90:- Long conceptual depth belongs in focused `references/` files.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/skill_creation.md:109:Smart-router resilience reference:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/skill_creation.md:115:❌ WRONG: File references or routing logic in "WHEN TO USE"
