.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/global/evergreen_packet_id_rule.md:12:## 1. OVERVIEW
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/global/evergreen_packet_id_rule.md:23:- Skill reference docs: `SKILL.md`, `ARCHITECTURE.md`, `references/**/*.md`
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/global/evergreen_packet_id_rule.md:26:- Configuration references: `ENV_REFERENCE.md`, `INSTALL_GUIDE.md`
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/global/evergreen_packet_id_rule.md:28:Skip this rule for spec-local docs (`spec.md`, `plan.md`, `tasks.md`, `checklist.md`, `implementation-summary.md`, `decision-record.md`, `handover.md`, `research-report.md`, `audit-findings.md`, `migration-plan.md`) — those ARE the packet record and naturally reference their own packet ID.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/global/evergreen_packet_id_rule.md:43:| Evergreen docs | `README.md`, `INSTALL_GUIDE.md`, `ARCHITECTURE.md`, `SKILL.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `references/**/*.md`, `feature_catalog/**/*.md`, `manual_testing_playbook/**/*.md`, `ENV_REFERENCE.md` | No |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/global/evergreen_packet_id_rule.md:45:Spec-local docs may reference packet numbers because they are the packet record. Evergreen docs must describe the shipped state by feature name, command, file path, and source anchor.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/global/evergreen_packet_id_rule.md:51:**❌ BAD evergreen references:**
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/global/evergreen_packet_id_rule.md:58:**✅ GOOD evergreen references:**
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/global/evergreen_packet_id_rule.md:62:- "See `references/config/hook_system.md` for the hook contract"
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/global/evergreen_packet_id_rule.md:64:**Why better:** Feature-name + source-anchor references stay valid after packet renumbering, archival, or consolidation.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/global/evergreen_packet_id_rule.md:70:When auditing evergreen docs, search candidate files for packet-history references before publishing:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/global/evergreen_packet_id_rule.md:86:- Link to the current reference document when the behavior is documented elsewhere.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/global/evergreen_packet_id_rule.md:102:- [skill_reference_template.md](../../assets/skill/skill_reference_template.md) — reference file structure (this file's own template)
