.opencode/skills/sk-doc/changelog/v1.5.0.0.md:3:First major iteration of `sk-doc` after the v1.3.0.0 series. Packet 102 ships five sequential phases that restructure the skill surface: reference relocation, a dedicated skill README asset, an agent identity rename across four runtime mirrors, manual playbook coverage for the renamed agent, and a single transactional remediation pass that closes every P1 and P2 finding from the phase-parent deep-review. All five phases land as additive child packets in `skilled-agent-orchestration/102-sk-doc-skill-readme-and-structure`. The `/create:*` command family stays surface-stable.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/changelog/v1.5.0.0.md:5:> Spec folder: `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/102-sk-doc-skill-readme-and-structure/{001-sk-doc-reference-relocation, 002-sk-doc-skill-readme-asset, 003-markdown-agent-rename, 004-sk-doc-playbook-markdown-agent-coverage, 005-deep-review-p1-p2-remediation}` (Level 2 phase parent, 5 phase children).
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/changelog/v1.5.0.0.md:13:The six sk-doc creation guides moved from `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/specific/` to the references root. SKILL.md smart routing, README related-documents, asset template links, manual playbook expected-resources, every `/create:*` command doc and YAML asset, and `graph-metadata.json` source-doc paths all point at the new root locations. The empty `specific/` directory is gone. Exact-match grep across the skill, agents, and commands surfaces returns zero stale `references/specific` matches.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/changelog/v1.5.0.0.md:19:A new `assets/skill/skill_readme_template.md` scaffold lands in the skill-creation flow alongside the SKILL.md and reference templates. The template structure aligns with `skill_asset_template.md` and opens with a short H1 intro, then `## 1. OVERVIEW`, `Purpose`, `Usage`, and `Location & Naming` before the content model. The `SKILL_CREATION` intent in SKILL.md now loads four resources instead of three, and `references/skill_creation.md` carries new README guidance. Folder README authoring continues to use `assets/readme/readme_template.md`. Skill-package README authoring uses the new dedicated asset.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/changelog/v1.5.0.0.md:25:The dedicated documentation executor agent renames from `@create` to `@markdown` across all four runtime mirrors: `.opencode/agents/markdown.md`, `.claude/agents/markdown.md`, `.gemini/agents/markdown.md`, and `.codex/agents/markdown.toml`. The Codex registry block updates from `[agents.create]` to `[agents.markdown]` with `config_file = "agents/markdown.toml"`. Orchestrator and code-agent references route documentation and component authoring through `@markdown`. The `/create:*` command family (`/create:agent`, `/create:sk-skill`, `/create:feature-catalog`, `/create:testing-playbook`, `/create:folder_readme`, `/create:changelog`) keeps every invocation unchanged because this is an agent identity rename, not a command-family rename.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/changelog/v1.5.0.0.md:37:A single `cli-codex gpt-5.5 / high / fast` dispatch closed all 16 findings from the 102 phase-parent deep-review in 129 seconds. Seven P1 status-sync and handoff issues plus nine P2 hygiene items resolved across nine files, with 26 checklist items marked. The parent `102/spec.md` carries a new Known Issues register that cross-references F-001, F-002, F-003 plus every new finding ID. The one structural P1 (cli-codex `@markdown` dispatch gap) resolved later in the same session via the inline-contract workaround documented under §Architecture below.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/changelog/v1.5.0.0.md:45:The `references/specific/` subdirectory was the only directory under references that grouped sk-doc creation guides separately from global standards. The relocation flattens that layer so creation guides sit at the same level as global standards under `references/`, with `global/` retained for the global-standards subset. YAML key names like `specific_creation` stay stable to avoid behavior changes outside path relocation.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/changelog/v1.5.0.0.md:71:| Stale `references/specific` search across skill, agents, commands          | PASS, zero matches                                  |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/changelog/v1.5.0.0.md:107:If a downstream consumer depended on the `references/specific/` path prefix for sk-doc creation guides, switch to the new root-level paths: `references/skill_creation.md`, `references/agent_creation.md`, `references/readme_creation.md`, `references/install_guide_creation.md`, `references/feature_catalog_creation.md`, `references/manual_testing_playbook_creation.md`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:3:Benchmark folder creation becomes the sixth sk-doc mode. The benchmark format mechanics that lived across three locations in system-spec-kit and sk-doc consolidate into a single canonical reference at references/benchmark_creation.md. A new SOURCE.md scaffold joins the benchmark_report_template.md in assets/benchmark/. The smart router gains BENCHMARK intent routing, and both SKILL.md and README.md update to reflect the six-mode surface.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:17:### Consolidated benchmark_creation.md reference
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:19:The trio of benchmark format docs collapsed into one canonical reference following the sk-doc *_creation.md pattern. The references/benchmarks/FORMAT.md file at 384 LOC, the references/benchmarks_format.md file at 205 LOC, and the assets template merged into references/benchmark_creation.md at 414 LOC with 10 numbered sections from OVERVIEW through RELATED RESOURCES. The consolidated doc generalizes the Section 5 example and Q7 to remove stack-specific references like Ollama, cat-24/409 and sentence-transformers so the guidance is portable across MCP skills. The mid-flight redesign was an operator decision after the first author pass.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:31:The BENCHMARK intent keywords extended to include benchmark creation, benchmark folder and source.md template while removing the deprecated benchmarks format keyword. The RESOURCE_MAP entry for BENCHMARK now loads three resources instead of two: references/benchmark_creation.md, assets/benchmark/benchmark_report_template.md and assets/benchmark/source_template.md. The Section 2 Resource Domains bullet list added assets/benchmark/ as a tracked domain for benchmark folder templates.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:41:| `references/benchmark_creation.md` | Created | 414 LOC, consolidates trio into *_creation.md pattern with 10 sections |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:42:| `references/benchmarks/FORMAT.md` | Deleted | 384 LOC moved into consolidated reference |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:43:| `references/benchmarks/` | Deleted | Empty directory after FORMAT.md removal |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:44:| `references/benchmarks_format.md` | Deleted | 205 LOC merged into consolidated reference |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:46:| `assets/benchmark/benchmark_report_template.md` | Modified | Cross-link to canonical reference updated |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:50:| `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/benchmarks/README.md` | Modified | 3 cross-links repointed to canonical reference |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:60:Operators with code that referenced the old benchmark format paths must update to the new canonical location. The references/benchmarks/FORMAT.md path, the references/benchmarks_format.md path, and both sibling skill FORMAT.md symlinks no longer exist. Update any references to `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/benchmarks/FORMAT.md` or `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/benchmarks/FORMAT.md` or `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/benchmarks_format.md` to point at `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/benchmark_creation.md`. There is no symlink fallback. Anything reading mcp_server/benchmarks/FORMAT.md directly will get a file-not-found error.

