/bin/zsh -lc "nl -ba .opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/frontmatter_templates.md | sed -n '1,180p'" in /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public
 succeeded in 0ms:
     1	---
     2	title: YAML Frontmatter Templates
     3	description: Templates and validation rules for YAML frontmatter across all document types in the OpenCode ecosystem.
     4	---
     5	
     6	# YAML Frontmatter Templates - Document Type Reference
     7	
     8	Templates and validation rules for YAML frontmatter by document type.
     9	
    10	---
    11	
    12	## 1. OVERVIEW
    13	
    14	### What Is YAML Frontmatter?
    15	
    16	**YAML frontmatter** is a metadata block at the beginning of markdown files, delimited by `---` markers. It provides machine-readable configuration that controls how AI agents and tools process the document.
    17	
    18	```yaml
    19	---
    20	name: skill-name
    21	description: What this skill does
    22	allowed-tools: Read, Write, Bash
    23	---
    24	
    25	# Document Content Starts Here
    26	```
    27	
    28	**Core Purpose**:
    29	- **Tool configuration** - Define which AI tools a skill/command can use
    30	- **Discovery** - Enable programmatic listing and searching of skills/commands
    31	- **Argument parsing** - Specify expected inputs for commands
    32	- **Metadata storage** - Version, category, tags for organization
    33	
    34	**Key Difference from Inline Metadata**:
    35	- YAML frontmatter = Machine-parseable, strict format, at file start
    36	- Inline metadata = Human-readable, flexible format, anywhere in document
    37	
    38	### Document Types and Frontmatter Requirements
    39	
    40	| Document Type | Frontmatter Required? | Reason |
    41	|---------------|----------------------|--------|
    42	| **SKILL.md** | ✅ **Required** | AI needs metadata to discover and invoke skills |
    43	| **Command** | ✅ **Required** | Arguments and tools must be declared |
    44	| **Knowledge** | ❌ **Forbidden** | Pure content, no programmatic interface |
    45	| **Spec** | ❌ **Not recommended** | Use inline metadata for flexibility |
    46	| **README** | ⚪ **Optional** | Usually none, unless documenting a skill |
    47	
    48	### Core Characteristics
    49	
    50	| Characteristic | Description |
    51	|----------------|-------------|
    52	| **Delimiter syntax** | Must start and end with `---` on separate lines |
    53	| **Position** | Must be at the very beginning of the file (line 1) |
    54	| **YAML format** | Key-value pairs, no nested objects for required fields |
    55	| **Single-line values** | Description must be on one line (parser limitation) |
    56	| **Case-sensitive** | Field names are lowercase (`name`, not `Name`) |
    57	
    58	### How Frontmatter Is Parsed
    59	
    60	```
    61	File loaded by OpenCode
    62	         │
    63	         ├─► Check line 1 for opening `---`
    64	         │   └─► Not found? → No frontmatter (may be error for SKILL/Command)
    65	         │
    66	         ├─► Find closing `---` (within first 20 lines)
    67	         │   └─► Not found? → Malformed frontmatter error
    68	         │
    69	         ├─► Parse YAML between delimiters
    70	         │   └─► Invalid YAML? → Parse error
    71	         │
    72	         └─► Validate required fields by document type
    73	             └─► Missing required? → Validation error
    74	```
    75	
    76	### Progressive Validation
    77	
    78	```
    79	Level 1: Structural Check
    80	         └─ Delimiters present and properly formatted
    81	            ↓
    82	Level 2: Field Presence
    83	         └─ Required fields exist for document type
    84	            ↓
    85	Level 3: Field Format
    86	         └─ Values match expected patterns (e.g., lowercase-with-hyphens)
    87	```
    88	
    89	---
    90	
    91	## 2. WHEN TO ADD FRONTMATTER
    92	
    93	### Add Frontmatter When
    94	
    95	**Programmatic Interface Needed**:
    96	- Document is a SKILL.md that AI agents invoke
    97	- Document is a command triggered via `/command-name`
    98	- Document needs tool restrictions (`allowed-tools`)
    99	- Document requires argument specification
   100	
   101	**Discovery Required**:
   102	- Skills/commands need to appear in listings
   103	- Metadata enables search and filtering
   104	- Version tracking needed
   105	
   106	**By Document Type**:
   107	
   108	| Document Type | Add Frontmatter? | Required Fields | Optional Fields |
   109	|---------------|------------------|-----------------|-----------------|
   110	| **SKILL.md** | ✅ Always | `name`, `description`, `allowed-tools` | `tags`, `category`, `version` |
   111	| **Command** | ✅ Always | `description`, `argument-hint`, `allowed-tools` | `name`, `model`, `version` |
   112	| **Knowledge** | ❌ Never | — | — |
   113	| **Spec** | ❌ Avoid | — | Use inline metadata instead |
   114	| **README** | ⚪ Rarely | Only if in `.opencode/skills/*/` | — |
   115	
   116	### Remove Frontmatter When
   117	
   118	**Content-Only Documents**:
   119	- Knowledge files (reference documentation)
   120	- Spec files (planning documents)
   121	- General markdown files
   122	
   123	**Why Remove from Knowledge/Spec**:
   124	- Frontmatter implies programmatic interface
   125	- These documents are pure content
   126	- Adds confusion about document purpose
   127	
   128	### Decision Framework
   129	
   130	```
   131	Is this document invoked programmatically?
   132	├─► YES
   133	│   │
   134	│   ├─► Is it a SKILL.md?
   135	│   │   └─► Add frontmatter: name, description, allowed-tools
   136	│   │
   137	│   └─► Is it a Command?
   138	│       └─► Add frontmatter: description, argument-hint, allowed-tools
   139	│
   140	└─► NO
   141	    │
   142	    ├─► Is it a Knowledge file?
   143	    │   └─► Remove frontmatter if present
   144	    │
   145	    ├─► Is it a Spec file?
   146	    │   └─► Remove frontmatter, use inline metadata
   147	    │
   148	    └─► Is it a README?
   149	        ├─► In .opencode/skills/*/? → Optional skill-style frontmatter
   150	        └─► Elsewhere? → No frontmatter needed
   151	```
   152	
   153	### Frontmatter Field Summary
   154	
   155	| Field | SKILL.md | Command | Purpose |
   156	|-------|----------|---------|---------|
   157	| `name` | ✅ Required | ⚪ Optional | Identifier (lowercase-with-hyphens) |
   158	| `description` | ✅ Required | ✅ Required | One-line explanation of purpose |
   159	| `allowed-tools` | ✅ Required | ✅ Required | Comma-separated tool list |
   160	| `argument-hint` | ❌ N/A | ✅ Required | Syntax hint: `<required> [optional]` |
   161	| `model` | ❌ N/A | ⚪ Optional | Override default model (rarely used) |
   162	| `version` | ⚪ Optional | ⚪ Optional | Semantic version |
   163	| `tags` | ⚪ Optional | ❌ N/A | Categorization keywords |
   164	
   165	---
   166	
   167	## 3. FIELD REFERENCE
   168	
   169	### `name` Field
   170	
   171	**Purpose**: Unique identifier for skills
   172	
   173	**Format Requirements**:
   174	- Pattern: `^[a-z][a-z0-9-]*$`
   175	- Style: `lowercase-with-hyphens`
   176	- Should match directory name
   177	
   178	**Examples**:
   179	```yaml
   180	# GOOD

