     1	---
     2	title: Evaluator Contract
     3	description: Deterministic scoring and benchmark contract for target-profiled deep-improvement experiments.
     4	---
     5	
     6	# Evaluator Contract
     7	
     8	Contract for how `deep-improvement` scores candidates and benchmarks packet-local outputs. Use it when you need the exact evaluator inputs, outputs, rubric dimensions, and hard rejection behavior.
     9	
    10	---
    11	
    12	## 1. OVERVIEW
    13	
    14	### Purpose
    15	
    16	Defines the input and output contract for the prompt-surface scorer and the output benchmark runner so deep-improvement runs remain deterministic enough for bounded local experimentation.
    17	
    18	### When to Use
    19	
    20	Use this reference when:
    21	- Updating scoring logic or benchmark rules
    22	- Explaining why a candidate was kept, rejected, or marked infra-failure
    23	- Adding a new target profile that needs evaluator support
    24	
    25	### Core Principle
    26	
    27	Weak candidates and infrastructure failures must be distinguishable. The contract exists so a broken tool path is not mistaken for a bad prompt and vice versa.
    28	
    29	---
    30	
    31	## 2. EVALUATED SURFACES
    32	
    33	### Dynamic Profiles (only mode)
    34	
    35	Every agent file in `.opencode/agents/*.md` is evaluated using dynamic mode. The scorer generates a profile on the fly from the agent's own structure, rules, and permissions using `generate-profile.cjs`. No static profiles are shipped; dynamic mode is the sole scoring path.
    36	
    37	---
    38	
    39	## 3. INPUT CONTRACT
    40	
    41	### Dynamic Mode (5-dimension, only mode)
    42	
    43	The scorer runs dynamic 5-dimension evaluation by default:
    44	- `--candidate=PATH` required (path to the agent .md file)
    45	- `--target=PATH` optional (defaults to candidate path)
    46	- `--manifest=PATH` optional
    47	- `--weights=JSON` optional (override default dimension weights)
    48	- `--output=PATH` optional
    49	
    50	The benchmark runner expects:
    51	- `--profile=ID`
    52	- `--outputs-dir=PATH`
    53	- `--output=PATH`
    54	- `--label=STRING` optional
    55	- `--state-log=PATH` optional
    56	
    57	---
    58	
    59	## 4. OUTPUT CONTRACT
    60	
    61	The scorer emits JSON with:
    62	- `status`
    63	- `profileId`
    64	- `family`
    65	- `evaluationMode` (always `"dynamic-5d"`)
    66	- `target`
    67	- `candidate`
    68	- `score` (weighted dynamic score)
    69	- `dimensions` (array of 5 dimension objects)
    70	- `recommendation`
    71	- `failureModes`
    72	- `legacyScore` (always `null`; retained for schema compatibility)
    73	
    74	The benchmark runner emits JSON with:
    75	- `status`
    76	- `profileId`
    77	- `family`
    78	- `label`
    79	- `aggregateScore`
    80	- `maxScore`

