     1	---
     2	title: Benchmark Operator Guide
     3	description: Step-by-step guide for running repeatable fixture benchmarks for deep-improvement target profiles.
     4	---
     5	
     6	# Benchmark Operator Guide
     7	
     8	Operational guide for running deep-improvement benchmarks against packet-local outputs. Use it when you need deterministic evidence that a target profile still behaves consistently across repeated runs.
     9	
    10	---
    11	
    12	## 1. OVERVIEW
    13	
    14	### Purpose
    15	
    16	Explains how to run deterministic fixture benchmarks, where to store the resulting evidence, and how to interpret repeatability.
    17	
    18	### When to Use
    19	
    20	Use this reference when:
    21	- Running the benchmark runner for any dynamic-mode target
    22	- Building repeatability evidence for a promotion gate
    23	- Checking whether a target profile is stable enough to trust
    24	
    25	### Core Principle
    26	
    27	Benchmark truth is output-based. The runner judges produced packet-local artifacts, not just how a prompt file reads.
    28	
    29	The copied runtime templates use the `improvement_*` asset names, but the packet-local runtime files produced by the current workflow use the `agent-improvement-*` naming family.
    30	
    31	---
    32	
    33	## 2. RUNNER COMMAND
    34	
    35	```text
    36	node .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs \
    37	  --profile .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-profiles/default.json \
    38	  --outputs-dir {spec_folder}/improvement/benchmark-outputs
    39	
    40	node .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/run-benchmark.cjs \
    41	  --profile .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-profiles/default.json \
    42	  --outputs-dir {spec_folder}/improvement/benchmark-outputs
    43	```
    44	
    45	### Scorer Selection
    46	
    47	`run-benchmark.cjs` defaults to `--scorer pattern` (the byte-identical heading and pattern matcher). Add `--scorer 5dim` to route the materialized outputs through the five-dimension scorer (`scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/score-model-variant.cjs`), and `--grader noop|mock|llm` to pick the D4 grader (default `noop`, deterministic). The report and `benchmark_run` record carry `scoringMethod: pattern` or `scoringMethod: 5dim`.
    48	
    49	```text
    50	node .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/run-benchmark.cjs \
    51	  --profile .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-profiles/default.json \
    52	  --outputs-dir {spec_folder}/improvement/benchmark-outputs \
    53	  --scorer 5dim --grader noop
    54	```
    55	
    56	### Integration Benchmark
    57	
    58	When running with an integration report, add the `--integration-report` flag:
    59	
    60	```text
    61	node scripts/model-benchmark/run-benchmark.cjs --profile .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-profiles/default.json --outputs-dir=... --integration-report=integration-report.json
    62	```
    63	
    64	The integration report adds `integrationScore` and `integrationDetails` to the benchmark output:
    65	- `mirrorScore` (0-100): deducts 30 per missing mirror, 20 per diverged mirror
    66	- `commandScore` (0/100): at least 1 command references the agent
    67	- `skillScore` (0/100): at least 1 skill references the agent
    68	- Weighted: 60% mirror + 20% command + 20% skill
    69	
    70	---
    71	
    72	## 3. REQUIRED LAYOUT
    73	
    74	```text
    75	{spec_folder}/improvement/benchmark-outputs/
    76	  fixture-baseline.md
    77	  fixture-improved.md
    78	  fixture-edge.md
    79	  report.json
    80	```

