.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/016-json-mode-hybrid-enrichment/001-initial-enrichment/research/iterations/iteration-001.md:42:8. **No V-rule validates YAML frontmatter well-formedness.**
.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/016-json-mode-hybrid-enrichment/001-initial-enrichment/research/iterations/iteration-001.md:43:   The V-rules parse specific YAML keys (title, spec_folder, trigger_phrases, key_topics) using custom regex-based extractors (`extractYamlValue`, `parseYamlList`). But there is **no rule that validates YAML syntax itself** -- a malformed frontmatter block (unclosed quotes, tab indentation, duplicate keys) will cause silent extraction failures where `extractYamlValue()` returns null without flagging an error. V3 checks for specific malformation patterns in `spec_folder` (bold markers, brackets), but the general case of broken YAML is uncovered.
.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/016-json-mode-hybrid-enrichment/001-initial-enrichment/research/iterations/iteration-001.md:51:    V12 (lines 612-650) reads `spec.md` from the filesystem to extract spec-level trigger_phrases. But `specFolder` extracted from YAML frontmatter may be a relative name (e.g., "016-json-mode-hybrid-enrichment") rather than an absolute path. The `path.resolve(specFolder, 'spec.md')` at line 618 resolves relative to CWD, which may not be the spec root. When the file is not found, V12 silently passes (no trigger_phrases = no check). This means V12 is a best-effort check that degrades to a no-op for many real invocations.
.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/016-json-mode-hybrid-enrichment/001-initial-enrichment/research/iterations/iteration-001.md:55:    A memory file with valid YAML frontmatter but a body consisting of only headers and no substantive text (e.g., all sections empty) passes all V-rules. V1 only checks for `[TBD]` in 4 specific fields. V5 only checks trigger_phrases when tool_count >= 5. There is no minimum content length or density check.
.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/016-json-mode-hybrid-enrichment/001-initial-enrichment/research/iterations/iteration-001.md:58:12. **Missing V-rule: No validation that `importance_tier` in frontmatter is a valid enum value.**
