.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/016-json-mode-hybrid-enrichment/003-field-integrity-and-schema/decision-record.md:19:    recent_action: "Backfilled _memory block (repo-wide frontmatter sweep)"
.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/016-json-mode-hybrid-enrichment/003-field-integrity-and-schema/decision-record.md:146:`extractFrontMatter` in `validate-memory-quality.ts` (lines 183-191) used a regex to parse YAML frontmatter blocks. YAML is not a regular language; the regex accepted malformed YAML (unclosed quotes, bad indentation, duplicate keys) without error and produced silently incorrect parsed values. This meant V-rules operating on frontmatter data could be making decisions on corrupted input. The `js-yaml` package is already a transitive dependency of the project.
.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/016-json-mode-hybrid-enrichment/003-field-integrity-and-schema/decision-record.md:150:- The replacement must handle the subset of YAML actually used in memory file frontmatter (string scalars, arrays of strings, simple key-value).
.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/016-json-mode-hybrid-enrichment/003-field-integrity-and-schema/decision-record.md:152:- Performance must be acceptable for typical frontmatter size (<50 lines).
.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/016-json-mode-hybrid-enrichment/003-field-integrity-and-schema/decision-record.md:173:**Why this one**: `js-yaml` is already present, covers all valid frontmatter syntax, and the synchronous API matches the existing function signature. There is no engineering cost beyond adding the import and the try/catch.
.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/016-json-mode-hybrid-enrichment/003-field-integrity-and-schema/decision-record.md:181:- V-rules operating on frontmatter data receive correct parsed values.
.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/016-json-mode-hybrid-enrichment/003-field-integrity-and-schema/decision-record.md:185:- Memories with previously-accepted malformed YAML will now fail the frontmatter V-rule. Mitigation: this is the correct behavior; those memories were silently storing incorrect metadata.
.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/016-json-mode-hybrid-enrichment/003-field-integrity-and-schema/decision-record.md:192:| `js-yaml` parse is slower than regex for very large frontmatter | L | Benchmark; typical frontmatter (<50 lines) parses in <2 ms |
.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/016-json-mode-hybrid-enrichment/003-field-integrity-and-schema/decision-record.md:203:| 4 | **Fits Goal?** | PASS | Goal is correct frontmatter parsing; `js-yaml` is the standard solution |
.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/016-json-mode-hybrid-enrichment/003-field-integrity-and-schema/decision-record.md:204:| 5 | **Open Horizons?** | PASS | Does not constrain future frontmatter schema changes |
.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/016-json-mode-hybrid-enrichment/003-field-integrity-and-schema/decision-record.md:316:The quality flag `short_content` exists in the codebase but no V-rule enforces a minimum content requirement. An empty payload `{}` combined with a CLI `spec-folder` argument produces a valid but useless memory: a frontmatter block with no body. These degenerate saves pollute the search index and consume storage without providing retrieval value. We needed to choose a threshold value that rejects genuinely trivial content without rejecting legitimate short memories such as tag collections or single-line decision records.
.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/016-json-mode-hybrid-enrichment/003-field-integrity-and-schema/decision-record.md:322:- Measurement must be taken after frontmatter is stripped (frontmatter itself is not content).
.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/016-json-mode-hybrid-enrichment/003-field-integrity-and-schema/decision-record.md:328:**We chose**: Reject memories whose body (after frontmatter strip) contains fewer than 50 non-whitespace characters, measured by removing all whitespace and counting remaining characters. Whitespace includes spaces, tabs, and newlines.
.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/016-json-mode-hybrid-enrichment/003-field-integrity-and-schema/decision-record.md:382:- `validate-memory-quality.ts`: Add content density V-rule using `CONTENT_DENSITY_MIN = 50` constant; compute non-whitespace length after frontmatter strip
.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/tasks.md:16:    recent_action: "Backfilled _memory block (repo-wide frontmatter sweep)"
